<HEADLINE>
<P>
USC FOOTBALL WATCH; 
</P>
<P>
AN INSIDE LOOK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE SPRINGER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A look back: The Trojans have reached one preseason goal, a third straight Rose 
Bowl berth, but they may have missed another by just five points. Their two 
losses (14-13 to Illinois in their opener and 28-24 to Notre Dame) have cost 
them a shot at a national championship. 
</P>
<P>
That was on the mind of defensive lineman Tim Ryan Saturday, amid the joy of 
the victorious USC locker room in Arizona. 
</P>
<P>
"We should have won the Illinois game," he said, "but if you're going to lose, 
it might as well be the first one. I've thought about the fact we wound up just 
five points away. It's not the first time I've just missed a championship. It's 
part of the sport. It hurts, but you've got to go on." 
</P>
<P>
A look ahead: With Gatorade residue still sticking to his hair from Saturday's 
postgame celebration, Trojan Coach Larry Smith threw out the first cliches for 
this week's USC-UCLA game. 
</P>
<P>
"It's always a big game," he said. "A super game. In this one, your previous 
accomplishments go out the window and you just play like heck." 
</P>
<P>
Playing hurt: Arizona's top rusher Saturday was fullback Mario Hampton, who 
gained 62 yards in only nine carries despite a broken hand. STEVE SPRINGER 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA111389-0046 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 134092 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
November 13, 1989, Monday, Home Edition 
</P>
