<P>
Philadelphia Exchange Extends Hours: The Philadelphia Stock Exchange plans to 
extend its trading day in foreign currency options by 6 1/2 hours to coincide 
with trading in Far East and Pacific countries. The exchange will remain open 
for foreign currency options from 10 p.m., its current close of evening 
trading, until 4:30 a.m., when it now begins its morning session. The new hours 
will begin in early 1990. 
</P>
