<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ORANGE; 
</P>
<P>
COUNCIL TO TAKE UP PROSPECT ST. PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council on Tuesday will consider a new proposal for the Prospect 
Street project, where a developer wants to build condominiums and single-family 
homes on a former gravel pit. 
</P>
<P>
The developer, Orange Homes, has plans for 485 condominiums and 73 houses on 
the old Conrock gravel pit. The Planning Commission recommended approval of the 
project. 
</P>
<P>
In July, 1988, the City Council unanimously rejected a proposal by a different 
developer, Silvercrest Corp., to bring 210 manufactured homes onto the site. 
</P>
<P>
The 70.8-acre site is west of Prospect Street, south of Collins Avenue, east of 
Santiago Creek and north of Walnut Avenue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
