<P>
PEDESTRIAN DIES AFTER BEING STRUCK BY VAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 74-year-old pedestrian died of injuries he suffered in a weekend traffic 
accident, police said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Officers said John Jakonen of Fountain Valley was walking across Bushard 
Street, just north of Garfield Avenue, about 6 p.m. Saturday when he was hit by 
a van as he stooped to pick up a newspaper he had dropped. 
</P>
<P>
Jakonen was rushed to Fountain Valley Regional Hospital and Medical Center but 
died shortly after the accident, police said. 
</P>
<P>
No charges or citations were filed, but the investigation is continuing, police 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
