<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
COUNCIL WILL WEIGH REZONING PROPOSALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council will decide tonight whether a number of properties on the 
Balboa Pennisula, around McFadden Square and in West Newport will be rezoned 
for low-density residential use. 
</P>
<P>
Most of the properties are currently zoned for commercial or high-density 
residential use. 
</P>
<P>
The rezoning, which would be effective 30 days after adoption, would affect new 
buildings and renovations to existing buildings. Owners also would be prevented 
from subdividing lots. 
</P>
<P>
Some residents have objected to the new zoning because it limits their building 
options. 
</P>
<P>
The Planning Commission initiated the rezoning to help limit the areas' density 
and voted unanimously in favor of it on Oct. 19. 
</P>
<P>
The council meets at 7:30 p.m. at Newport Beach City Hall. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
